"n./v.漫步，缓行 【英】 n. / v. 漫步，缓行(walk in a leisurely manner) 【考】 walk : amble / talk : chat(漫步是无目的的走/ 闲聊是无目的的聊) 【记】 amble=ambul(走路) 【同】 同根词: ambulance(救护车); preamble(前言, 序言)近形词: ample(丰富的); ramble(漫步, 闲逛) n. /v. 漫步, 缓行(尤指马步) = saunter = bummel = mosey = stroll 【例】The horse is walking at an amble 这匹马正在溜蹄行走. 【根】amble = ambul走anble = I am ball: 我是球, 所以只能漫步 【参】ambulance(n 救护车); preamble(n 前言, 序言) 【区】ample(adj 充足的, 丰富的)－象apple－充足的ramble(v 漫游n 漫游)－因为比amble多r = run, 所以漫游的范围广 【类】walk: amble = talk: chat = draw: doodle无目的的走是漫步 = 无目的的聊是闲聊 = 无目的的画是乱画tint: suffuse = amble: wander轻微着色: 弥漫充满 = 缓行, 溜达: 漫游, 徘??(程度) 【反】match quickly(快速追上) 【记】音：安步，安步当车, 安详地缓缓步行；接近漫步，散步的发音； 【相关】ambulance 救护车，ambulate 走动，结尾发音是步的词：amble，ramble 漫步，散步，preamble( introductory statement),scramble 爬行，shamble(音：跚步)蹒跚地走 amble (v.)  early 14c., from Old French ambler ""walk as a horse does,"" from Latin ambulare ""to walk, to go about, take a walk,"" perhaps a compound of ambi- ""around"" (see ambi-) and -ulare, from PIE root *el- ""to go"" (cognates: Greek ale ""wandering,"" alaomai ""wander about;"" Latvian aluot ""go around or astray""). Until 1590s used only of horses or persons on horseback. Related: Ambled; ambling. As a noun, from late 14c."
